HEADWORD: Ferranti mains
<hw>Fer*ran"ti
mains"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A form of
conductor, designed by <etsep>Ferranti</etsep>, for currents of high
potential, and consisting of concentric tubes of copper separated by an
